(38, 1, '2011-05-24 22:02:55', '2011-05-24 22:02:55', 'We work hard to help people. As you can tell from looking through our website, we want you to be informed.  We want you to make smart choices. Very few people are happy at the end of the divorce process, but hopefully our clients understand the process, why we made the choices we did, and feel confident in the results.\n\nOur focus is to keep your focus on what’s important. By doing that, you’ll not only save money but you’ll also get better results. We know how hard it can be to focus on reasonable objectives in highly emotional cases, but it can be done as you make positive and informed choices.\n\nFamily law is a hard choice for a lawyer, given the high degree of conflict and the emotions involved. But we have chosen this field of law because we know we can make a difference, in a very personal and real way, for countless people and their kids. We feel good about the job we do because every day, we make that difference.\n<h2>Team Approach</h2>\nWhen you meet with a lawyer on our staff you should know that the entire firm will be working with that lawyer in your interests.  We generally assign two lawyers to each case so we can keep the costs down by assigning some work to a less expensive lawyer and to be sure there is extra coverage, should it be needed.\n\nIn addition, a paralegal is assigned to the file to handle the day to day tasks and to make sure that some tasks are billed at a lower rate.\n\nFinally, every week our lawyers meet to discuss cases and issues. They are educational in nature and allow us to share strategies and experience.\n<h2>Technology</h2>\nFor many law firms, it makes absolutely no sense to be more efficient – the longer the lawyers spend doing a task, the more money the law firm makes. Why invest in mechanisms that create fewer billable hours?\n\nWe think that’s nonsense. We want our clients to be happy with our performance. We want them to know we earned our fee and were sensitive to their budgets.\n\nThat’s why we invest heavily in technology to make our lawyers and staff more productive:\n<ul>\n	<li>All files are digital</li>\n	<li>Our primary means of communicating with clients is via email</li>\n	<li>Email is delivered to our phones 24 hours a day</li>\n	<li>Voicemails are sent to us by email as well as being kept on our phones</li>\n	<li>Secure access allows us to work anywhere in the world, any time of day</li>\n</ul>\nIn many ways, we’ve pioneered the use of technology in Utah family law firms. And we continue to push the limits of technology because we believe being more efficient lets us focus on what’s really important and what we love to do – advocate for clients in family law cases.\n<h2>The Great Contradiction</h2>\nMany law firms operate by placing pressure on their lawyers to bill an insane amount of hours every month. At the same time the firm is trying to bill the client all these hours, the interest of the client may be best served by not letting the lawyer engage in all the work.\n\nFor example, at a settlement conference a client may best be served by taking a deal. Yet, the lawyer may best be served by rejecting the deal, stirring up a fight, and meeting his or her billable hourly goal for the next few months.\n\nOf course lawyers are ethically bound to act in a client’s best interests at all times – even when the interests of the client may conflict with the lawyer’s own personal goals. But when a law firm places so much emphasis on the billable hour, and a young lawyer’s fate may be determined by this one case, a great contradiction exists.\n\nAt our law firm, we completely separate a lawyer’s compensation from the fees a lawyer collects. Collecting a fee is left to other administrative staff members and only in extreme situations of last resort does the lawyer become involved.\n\nWe feel this approach allows lawyers to be lawyers and to focus on one thing only – doing the best thing for the client.\n<h2>Strong &amp; Hanni''s History</h2>\nFor more than a century, the law firm of Strong &amp; Hanni has steadily built a foundation of in-depth legal knowledge coupled with vast practical experience. Combined with the incorporation of today’s state-of-the-art technology, it is easy to see why Strong &amp; Hanni is one of the highest rated and most formidable law firms in the Intermountain West. We are also strategically positioned to continue to be one of the west’s most dynamic law firms during our next hundred years. Strong &amp; Hanni’s Martindale-Hubbell AV Rating, along with a number of our attorneys being inducted into the American College of Trial Lawyers, demonstrates exceptional legal ability and superior quality in every aspect of our firm.\n\nStrong &amp; Hanni forged its reputation in the courtroom as accomplished and experienced trial attorneys. While our lawyers spend significant time doing trial work, we also recognize the importance of resolving disputes in an efficient and cost effective manner through the use of arbitration, mediation and other alternative dispute resolution methods. Regardless of the forum, Strong &amp; Hanni provides its clients with aggressive representation. Strong &amp; Hanni prides itself on our attorneys’ ability to handle the many types of complex litigation our clients have.\n\nAs a full service law firm, Strong &amp; Hanni provides a wide range of business, corporate and personal legal services. We realize that your legal and business needs can best be served by taking the time to understand the unique nature of your business, personal circumstances, goals, concerns, and objectives. Strong &amp; Hanni sets itself apart through implementing proven technologies and practices. We value the relationship we have with our clients and we provide creative and cost effective solutions to help them achieve their goals. We are proud to provide a vast array of business services including consulting, contracts, business formation, mergers and acquisitions, securities, tax, real estate, and estate planning.', 'The Firm', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-autosave', '', '', '2011-05-24 22:02:55', '2011-05-24 22:02:55', '', 2, 'http://clients.edit.com/801divorce/draft6/2010/09/23/2-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
