(222, 1, '2011-04-27 21:11:26', '2011-04-27 21:11:26', 'A Premarital Agreement, also commonly referred to as a Prenuptial or Antenuptial Agreement, is a contract entered into by the parties before marriage.  Such an agreement defines what will happen when the marriage ends, either by dissolution or the death of one of the parties.\r\n\r\nA Postnuptial Agreement is an agreement that spouses may enter into after they are married in circumstances where they choose to remain married but want to divide their assets or provide for a specific division in the event of dissolution of marriage or death.\r\n\r\nParties contemplating these agreements need lawyers who understand the delicate balance necessary for the marriage to occur or be preserved when negotiating for the financial results the parties seek to achieve.  Strong and Hanni has lawyers with extensive experience in dealing with the fine line between negotiating a favorable financial settlement while preserving the parties’ relationship.\r\n\r\nPlease call 801-Divorce (348-6723) for more information.', 'Premarital and Postnuptial Agreements', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'premarital-and-postnuptial-agreements', '', '', '2011-04-27 21:42:33', '2011-04-27 21:42:33', '', 14, 'http://clients.edit.com/801divorce/draft6/?page_id=222', 100, 'page', '', 0),
