(285, 1, '2011-04-27 21:46:23', '2011-04-27 21:46:23', 'Your child’s parenting schedule should never be “cookie-cutter.”  Parenting time schedules should be carefully thought out and developed to meet the needs of your kids.  Yet sometimes it can be helpful to have a place to start.  That’s why we’ve pulled together some common plans that our divorce lawyers use frequently as a place to begin the discussion about schedules.  Our <a href="http://www.denverfamilies.com/attorney-bios/" target="_blank">attorneys</a> often take these schedules as a basis and build from them to develop custom plans that work for clients and their children.\r\n<h3>Infinite Parent Time Possibilities</h3>\r\nThere are seriously an infinite number of possible parenting time schedules. Since parents know their, and their kid’s, schedules much better than <a href="http://www.denverfamilies.com/attorney-bios/" target="_blank">lawyers</a> and judges, it’s a very wise move to work out this schedule yourselves instead of leaving it to us.\r\n\r\nNumber one, it can be very expensive for <a href="http://www.denverfamilies.com/attorney-bios/" target="_blank">lawyers</a> to learn their client’s, and their client’s kid’s, schedules. And secondly, we’re bound to come up with a plan that will be less than optimal than one you could work out yourselves.\r\n\r\nWith that said, below are some examples of commonly used schedules. We’ve rated them for the what we call the <a href="http://www.denverfamilies.com/custody/two-pillars/" target="_blank">two pillars</a> of parenting time, frequency and consistency. These are ONLY samples! If you chose to use them at all in your decision making process, you should only use them as a place to start!', 'Parent Time', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '234-revision-3', '', '', '2011-04-27 21:46:23', '2011-04-27 21:46:23', '', 234, 'http://clients.edit.com/801divorce/draft6/2011/04/27/234-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
