(306, 1, '2011-04-27 22:19:59', '2011-04-27 22:19:59', 'Divorces often present tax issues and problems, including those relating to property division, spousal support, child support, and sometimes previously filed (or yet to be filed) tax returns.  Whenever possible, we advocate for settlements or final judgments that do not waste assets through the triggering of unnecessary income, estate, or gift tax costs.  A goal in many cases is to maximize the after-tax dollars to the firm’s client while at the same time preserving each party’s estate.  Strong and Hanni has lawyers who are recognized as experts in divorce tax and financial planning.\n\nPlease call 801-Divorce (348-6723) for more information.', 'Tax and Financial Planning in The Context Of Divorce', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '249-autosave', '', '', '2011-04-27 22:19:59', '2011-04-27 22:19:59', '', 249, 'http://clients.edit.com/801divorce/draft6/2011/04/27/249-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
