thly basis to determine how we can improve our service. One of the things mentioned most often by new clients is how much they appreciate the consistent communication from our attorneys, paralegals, and administrative staff. As a valued client, your legal team will strive to communicate with you and keep you updated about the developments of your case.\r\n\r\nWe are committed to the idea that clients should be as informed as possible about their legal rights. Several of our attorneys have authored numerous, published articles about family law. Bryant J. McConkie and David W. Read are founding editors of the Utah State Bar’s Utah Journal of Family Law.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Cost Control</strong>\r\nAlthough our rates are similar to other firms, we are generally less expensive than our competitors for three (3) important reasons:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li> Aggressive attorneys and angry spouses can escalate situations that will dramatically increase legal fees, but we employ techniques and processes to help diffuse these situations. Your attorney will strategize with you in order to achieve an expedient and satisfactory settlement to save you time, money, and aggravation.</li>\r\n	<li> Focusing exclusively on family law makes us more efficient.</li>\r\n	<li> Using the latest technology allows our attorneys to work quickly and efficiently, which means saving you time and money.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>', 'Why Call 801-Divorce?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '326-revision-2', '', '', '2011-04-27 22:47:53', '2011-04-27 22:47:53', '', 326, 'http://clients.edit.com/801divorce/draft6/2011/04/27/326-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
