ing only – doing the best thing for the client.\r\n<h2>Strong &amp; Hanni''s History</h2>\r\nFor more than a century, the law firm of Strong &amp; Hanni has steadily built a foundation of in-depth legal knowledge coupled with vast practical experience. Combined with the incorporation of today’s state-of-the-art technology, it is easy to see why Strong &amp; Hanni is one of the highest rated and most formidable law firms in the Intermountain West. We are also strategically positioned to continue to be one of the west’s most dynamic law firms during our next hundred years. Strong &amp; Hanni’s Martindale-Hubbell AV Rating, along with a number of our attorneys being inducted into the American College of Trial Lawyers, demonstrates exceptional legal ability and superior quality in every aspect of our firm.\r\n\r\nStrong &amp; Hanni forged its reputation in the courtroom as accomplished and experienced trial attorneys. While our lawyers spend significant time doing trial work, we also recognize the importance of resolving disputes in an efficient and cost effective manner through the use of arbitration, mediation and other alternative dispute resolution methods. Regardless of the forum, Strong &amp; Hanni provides its clients with aggressive representation. Strong &amp; Hanni prides itself on our attorneys’ ability to handle the many types of complex litigation our clients have.\r\n\r\nAs a full service law firm, Strong &amp; Hanni provides a wide range of business, corporate and personal legal services. We realize that your legal and business needs can best be served by taking the time to understand the unique nature of your business, personal circumstances, goals, concerns, and objectives. Strong &amp; Hanni sets itself apart through implementing proven technologies and practices. We value the relationship we have with our clients and we provide creative and cost effective solutions to help them achieve their goals. We are proud to provide a vast array of business services including consulting, contracts, business formation, mergers and acquisitions, securities, tax, real estate, and estate planning.', 'The Firm', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-36', '', '', '2011-05-24 22:05:40', '2011-05-24 22:05:40', '', 2, 'http://clients.edit.com/801divorce/draft6/2011/05/24/2-revision-36/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(379, 1, '2011-04-29 21:39:25', '2011-04-29 21:39:25', '<h1>Schedule a Consultation with Utah''s Family Law Team</h1>\r\nFill out the form below, or call: 801-Divorce (348-6723) to schedule your consultation.  If you are considering legal action for a family law matter in the State of Utah, we recommend that you consult with an attorney who will help you understand your rights and options according to Utah law.\r\n\r\nWe are licensed attorneys to serve clients throughout the State of Utah.\r\n(We respectfully request that you do not bring children to your consultation)\r\n\r\n<em><strong>DISCLAIMER</strong></em><em>: No attorney - client relationship will be created by virtue of information, facts or questions you provide by submitting this form. The general information given in this website is intended to be a starting point only by describing general aspects of the law, and it is important that you consult with an attorney with regard to your specific legal rights.</em>', 'Schedule a Consultation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '26-revision-7', '', '', '2011-04-29 21:39:25', '2011-04-29 21:39:25', '', 26, 'http://clients.edit.com/801divorce/draft6/2011/04/29/26-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
